Author: 

Raghu Udiyar <raghusiddarth@gmail.com>

Description:

Runs CISCO IOS commands on a remote cisco switch non-interactively using an ssh connection

Requires :

Pexpect : http://www.noah.org/pexpect

Usage:

$ ./switch-control.py --help
usage: switch-control.py [-h] [-u USERNAME] [-p PASSWORD] [-v]
                         (-i | -c COMMAND | -f FILE)
                         hostname

Runs CISCO IOS commands on a remote cisco switch non-interactively using a ssh
connection. The commands can be either read from the commandline or a file.
For debugging set DEBUG=1, debug output will be written to LOGFILE

positional arguments:
  hostname              switch hostname

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -u USERNAME, --username USERNAME
                        switch username
  -p PASSWORD, --password PASSWORD
                        switch password
  -v, --version         show program's version number and exit
  -i, --interactive     enter interactive mode (not implemented)
  -c COMMAND, --command COMMAND
                        specify the command to run
  -f FILE, --file FILE  read commands from a file

Notes:

For running the configure command you may need to change the prompt a bit.
Check the comments in source to figure out where to make the changes
